    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ 395\u00b0F/ Gas 6</p> <p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Boil a kettle, then slice</span> the\u00a0<strong>seasonal squash</strong>\u00a0in half and scoop out the seeds,\u00a0discarding them</p> <p>Tip:<span class=\"text-highlight\"> for</span> easier chopping, use a bread <span class=\"text-highlight\">knife (oiling the knife helps too!)</span></p> <p>Note: our seasonal squashes will come in <span class=\"text-highlight\">all colours, shapes and sizes, but don't worry \u2013 the method will stay the same!</span></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice each\u00a0<strong>squash</strong>\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span> into 1cm wedges</p> <p>Add the <strong>squash wedges</strong>\u00a0to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 20-22 min or until softened\u00a0with a slight bite</p> <p>Meanwhile, strip the<strong> sage leaves</strong> and chop them finely, discarding the stems</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p> <p>Add\u00a0the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>smoked streaky</strong></span>\u00a0<strong>bacon</strong>\u00a0and cook for 3-4 min or until crisp, turning once halfway\u00a0</p> <p>Once crisp, transfer it to a plate and set aside</p> <p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the\u00a0<strong>gnocchi\u00a0</strong>to a pot of<strong>\u00a0boiled water\u00a0</strong>with a large pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Cook the<strong>\u00a0gnocchi</strong>\u00a0for 3 min or until it begins to rise to the top of the pot</p> <p>Once done, drain the\u00a0<strong>gnocchi</strong>, reserving a cup of the\u00a0<strong>starchy cooking water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe the bacon pan clean with <strong>kitchen paper </strong>and return it to a medium heat</p> <p>Add 50g\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[100g]</span>\u00a0<strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped sage</strong> and cook for 2 min or until foaming and beginning to turn a light brown colour \u2013 this is your <strong>sage burnt butter</strong></p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, break the <strong>crispy <span class=\"text-highlight\">bacon</span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">\u00a0into s</span>hards (clean hands is the best way!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained gnocchi </strong>to the\u00a0<strong>sage burnt butter </strong>with the\u00a0<strong>roasted</strong>\u00a0<strong>squash wedges</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p> <p>Season\u00a0with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and\u00a0a very generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p> <p>Tip: add a small splash of <strong>starchy cooking water</strong> if the sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/squash-and-sage-gnocchi-with-bacon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Wash the <strong>wild rocket</strong> and pat it dry</span></p> <p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Serve the<strong>\u00a0squash &amp; sage gnocchi</strong>\u00a0topped with the <strong>bacon shards</strong>,<strong> rocket\u00a0</strong>and the <strong>remaining cheese</strong></span></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
